1 PREFACE

1.1 PROJECT

Explore influence of political system on policy stringency and severity of COVID epidemic in individual countries.

1.2 OBJECTIVE

protoype analysis between stringency, COVID infections and deaths and political system

1.5 Set Global Varibales

> DIR="/home/rstudio/NONWORK/HackathonUCL_2020-1/rstuff/"

> INPUTFOLDER=paste0(DIR,"/data/input/")
> SCRIPT="S01"
> DATE=Sys.Date()

2 Load and Format Oxford Government Response data

Data Source: https://github.com/OxCGRT/covid-policy-tracker

2.1 Load latest data version from github

> datain = fread("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OxCGRT/covid-policy-tracker/master/data/OxCGRT_latest.csv")

2.2 Save local copy

> write_csv(datain,
+           paste0(OUTFOLDER, SCRIPT, ".oxford_government_reponse_latest.", DATE, ".csv.gz"))

2.2.1 Glimpse at initial data, look at 10 random data rows

> datain %>% 
+   sample_n(size=10) %>% myDT()

2.3 Select Nationwide data and drop regional data

> data_nationwide = datain %>% 
+   filter(Jurisdiction == "NAT_TOTAL")

2.4 Select data available till 1st of June 2021

> data_natiowide_june_1st = data_nationwide %>% 
+   filter(Date=="20210601")

3 Make first map

3.1 Total death COVID numbers till 1st of June 2021

> world_map <- map_data("world")
> plot_data01 = world_map %>% 
+   left_join(data_natiowide_june_1st[,c("CountryName", "ConfirmedDeaths")], 
+             by=c("region"="CountryName"))
> 
> ggplot(plot_data01, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group)) +
+   geom_polygon(aes(fill = ConfirmedDeaths ), color = "white")+
+   scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "C") +
+   theme_void()

3.2 Policy Stringency Index 1st of June 2021

> plot_data02 = world_map %>% 
+   left_join(data_natiowide_june_1st[,c("CountryName", "StringencyIndex")], 
+             by=c("region"="CountryName"))
> 
> ggplot(plot_data02, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group)) +
+   geom_polygon(aes(fill = StringencyIndex ), color = "white")+
+   scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "C") +
+   theme_void()

4 Load further annotation data

Sources: - population numbers for 2020: https://www.worldometers.info/world-population/population-by-country/ - democracy index and government type: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democracy_Index

> annotation = fread(paste0(INPUTFOLDER, "further_annotations.csv"))

4.1 look at annotations for some examplary countries

> annotation %>% myDT()

4.2 Combine with Oxford data

> data_natiowide_june_1st_annotation = data_natiowide_june_1st %>% 
+   inner_join(annotation, by="CountryName")

5 Analysis Influence of Governement System on Policy Stringency

5.1 Plot Government System for chosen countries

> plot_data03 = world_map %>% 
+   left_join(data_natiowide_june_1st_annotation[,c("CountryName", "Government_Style", "StringencyIndex")], 
+             by=c("region"="CountryName"))
> 
> ggplot(plot_data03, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group)) +
+   geom_polygon(aes(fill = Government_Style ), color = "white")+
+   theme_void()

5.2 Compare Policy Stringency

> ggplot(plot_data03, aes(x=Government_Style, y=StringencyIndex,
+                         color=Government_Style)) +
+    theme_bw() +
+   #geom_point(position=position_jitter(width=0.3), alpha=0.6) +
+   geom_boxplot(size=1.4,fill=NA, outlier.size=0) +
+   geom_boxplot(size=1.4,fill=NA, outlier.size=0, color=alpha("black",0.3)) +
+  
+     # change titles here:
+   #labs(y="Y Axis title", x="X Axis Title", title="Title") +
+   theme(title = element_text(size=rel(1.3), face = "bold"),
+         axis.title.y = element_text(vjust=1.5),
+         axis.title.x = element_text(vjust=-1.5),
+         axis.text = element_text(size=rel(1.25)),
+         axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30,hjust = 1),
+         legend.text = element_text(size=rel(1.3)),
+         strip.text = element_text(size=rel(1.3)),
+         plot.margin = unit(c(1,1,1,2), "cm"),
+         panel.grid.major = element_line(colour="grey60"))
